definitions.definition: Of a flower, or the plant bearing it: having the stamens fused together at least partly by the filaments so that they form two separate bundles , or a bundle and a lone separate stamen.

main_definition: ( botany ) Of a flower, or the plant bearing it: having the stamens fused together at least partly by the filaments so that they form two separate bundles , or a bundle and a lone separate stamen.
